{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4eb16bd6-17ed-4e2a-8df9-1e0cd8347af3","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically when you save a file\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — only run tests whose name contains the given string\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so you don't need the full namespace. You can also filter by just the method name:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"Name=ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1e18359c-912c-46f7-b81d-ff65066bc31f","outputTokens":164,"requestId":"9819:2E6B36:1135D95:15916D0:69FFE3D6"},"id":"4b2109f3-ab11-4fa4-b180-de65f032b77e","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:48:10.564Z","parentId":"7d64fea5-3d43-4a16-a2c8-c11f30a453e1"}
